}}
Although it was built as a replacement for Grant Park's outdoor concert facilities, larger annual events such as the [[Chicago Blues Festival|Chicago Blues]] and [[Chicago Jazz Festival]]s and [[Taste of Chicago]] are too large for Jay Pritzker Pavilion and continue to be held in and around Petrillo Music Shell.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:ADHB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=103E19F511C0251F&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Pritzker hitting the right notes with local music&nbsp;<U+2013> organizations |accessdate=2009-11-15|date=2004-07-09|page=36|work=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]|author=Guarino, Mark}}</ref><ref name = "Fodors"/> The pavilion has hosted smaller festivals, such as the Chicago Gospel Music Festival, since 2005.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:FJLB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=10B113D48A583568&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Taste of Chicago kicks off festival season|accessdate=2009-11-15|date=2005-05-15|page=G04|work=[[The Flint Journal]]|author=Mink, Randy}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CSTB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=112006C2E0C4EA80&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Winans adds luster to eclectic Gospel fest|accessdate=2009-11-15|date=2006-06-02|page=NV46|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|author=Hoekstra, Dave}}</ref> Public opinion has been in favor of moving some of the smaller Blues and Jazz festival events to the pavilion, with its better, more modern acoustics.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CTRB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=111E5EF9535776AD&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=How Millennium Park created a unique nexus of culture|accessdate=2009-11-15|date=2006-05-28|page=1, Arts & Entertainment section|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|author=Reich, Howard}}</ref> By 2009, as the city grappled with a budget deficit, it considered realigning parts of the larger festivals and made definite plans to move some of the smaller ones to the more modern venue.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CTRB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=12BB5D88DBC880C8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Creative thinking could save Chicago's music festivals|accessdate=2009-11-15|date=2009-11-01|page=1, Arts & Entertainment section|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|author=Reich, Howard}}</ref>

On July 18, 2007, the Grant Park Music Festival partnered with the [[Metro Chicago]] to produce a free Wednesday-night show celebrating Metro's 25th anniversary and featuring [[Independent music|indie band]] [[The Decemberists]] with the Grant Park Orchestra.<ref name=AmmftMOD>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:ADHB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11A98191B5675748&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=A musical merger for the Millennium Orchestra, Decemberists&nbsp;<U+2013> draw all ages|accessdate=2009-11-20|date=2007-07-19|work=[[Daily Herald (Arlington Heights)|Daily Herald]]|page=18|author=Pizek, Jeff}}</ref><ref name=OaltDs>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CSTB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11A7D408DB6AC898&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Orchestra adds little to Decemberists' show&nbsp;<U+2013> But give stellar Pritzker Pavilion kudos for giving rock act a chance|accessdate=2009-11-20|date=2007-07-19|work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|page=36|author=DeRogatis, Jim}}</ref> The show featured new orchestral arrangements of The Decemberists' songs by Sean O'Loughlin, who also conducted in lieu of Kalmar.<ref name=AmmftMOD/><ref name=OaltDs/> While the concert was free,<ref name=OaltDs/> the front seating sections were reserved for season membership holders; fans of the band got the remaining seats or sat on the lawn. This led Decemberists' frontman [[Colin Meloy]] to encourage the crowd to breach the barriers between the seats and Great Lawn to get closer to the stage for the band's encore performance, which was without the orchestra. Estimated attendance was 11,000 to 15,000, the largest for any free concert at the pavilion to date.<ref name=OaltDs/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://chicagoist.com/2007/07/19/the_decemberist.php|title=ReViewed: The Decemberists with the Grant Park Orchestra|accessdate=2008-06-09|date=2007-07-19|work=Chicagoist}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CTRB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=11A8233D86E3AFE8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=Decemberists can strike without the band|accessdate=2009-11-20|date=2007-07-20|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|page=1, Tempo section|author=Kot, Greg}}</ref>

Other events include a concert by [[Wilco]] on September 12, 2007, the "Poland for Chicago" show with Polish President [[Lech Kaczy<U+0144>ski]] on September 25, 2007, and a [[global warming]] awareness festival which culminated in a performance entitled ''Arctic'' at the pavilion in November 2007.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailyherald.com/story/?id=37198|accessdate=2007-09-21|publisher= Daily Herald Inc|title=Wilco just perfect at Millennium Park concert|author=Cox, Ted}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.millenniumpark.org/parkevents/eventpopup.aspx?eventId=586|accessdate=2007-09-21|title=Poland for Chicago|publisher=City of Chicago}} {{Dead link|date=April 2012|bot=H3llBot}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/7b21456e-920d-11dc-8981-0000779fd2ac.html|title=Arctic: Soundscape|accessdate=2008-07-31|date=2007-11-13|publisher=The Financial Times Ltd|work=[[The Financial Times]]|author=Weitzman, Hal | format = subscription required }}</ref> Most events at the pavilion remain free; the only public event at the pavilion in the summer of 2008 that charged admission was a concert by [[Rogue Wave (band)|Rogue Wave]] and [[Death Cab for Cutie]] on June 3.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://articles.chicagotribune.com/2008-06-05/features/0806040159_1_narrow-stairs-death-cab-ben-gibbard|accessdate=2008-06-09|publisher= Chicago Tribune|title=Death Cab rolls on|author=Kot, Greg|date=2008-06-05}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CTRB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=12109FA59B4B9450&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=0D0CB579A3BDA420|title=2008 Summer Calendar&nbsp;<U+2013> The Sky's The Limit&nbsp;<U+2013> All the music, dancing, wonderment and corn on the cob your heart desires are in our comprehensive guide to hot-weather fun. So get out there! |accessdate=2009-11-15|date=2008-06-01|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|page=35, Magazine section}}</ref> The pavilion has hosted several one-day events that were noted in international publications, including the United States debut of ''[[A Throw of Dice]]'', a 1929 Indian [[silent movie]] about two kings with a common love interest, on July 30, 2008. At the debut, [[Nitin Sawhney]] and the Grant Park Orchestra accompanied the movie with a live performance.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.nytimes.com/2008/07/27/travel/27DATEBOOK.html?|title=Datebook: Chicago, San Francisco and Singapore|accessdate=2008-07-30|date=2008-07-27|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|work=[[The New York Times]]}}</ref> [[Oprah Winfrey]] filmed the September 8, 2008, season-opening ''[[The Oprah Winfrey Show|Oprah Winfrey Show]]'' on September 3, 2008, at the pavilion with more than 150 [[Olympic medal]]ists, including [[Michael Phelps]], [[Nastia Liukin]], [[Dara Torres]], [[Kobe Bryant]], [[Misty May-Treanor]] and [[Kerri Walsh]], in an effort to rally support for the [[Chicago 2016 Olympic bid]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.suntimes.com/sports/olympics/1136773,CST-NWS-oprah30.article|title=Oprah tickets available for show featuring Olympians|accessdate=2008-09-01|date=2008-08-30|publisher=Digital Chicago, Inc |work=[[Chicago Sun-Times]]|author=Herrmann, Andrew|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080903021819/http://www.suntimes.com/sports/olympics/1136773,CST-NWS-oprah30.article <!--Added by H3llBot-->|archivedate=2008-09-03}}</ref>

[[File:20100228 Pritzker Pavilion Chicago Winter Dance 2010.JPG|left|thumb|Chicago Winter Dance participants]]
Concerts performed by the Grant Park Orchestra and directed by Kalmar were part of a June 19, 2009, citywide [[Burnham Plan]] centennial celebration that included the unveiling of the [[Burnham Pavilion]] elsewhere in the park.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CTRB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=128EE0094C72FF18&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=AA98CDC331574F0ABEAFF732B33DC0B2|title=John von Rhein recommends&nbsp;<U+2013> Classical corner |accessdate=2009-06-21|date=2009-06-19|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://docs.newsbank.com/openurl?ctx_ver=z39.88-2004&rft_id=info:sid/iw.newsbank.com:NewsBank:CTRB&rft_val_format=info:ofi/fmt:kev:mtx:ctx&rft_dat=128EE00911C6ACA8&svc_dat=InfoWeb:aggregated5&req_dat=AA98CDC331574F0ABEAFF732B33DC0B2|title=Burnham's Plan inspires a king-sized choral opus |accessdate=2009-06-21|date=2009-06-19|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]|author=von Rhein, John}}</ref> The concert featured the world premiere of [[Michael Torke]]'s work for [[symphony]] and [[choir|chorus]] entitled ''Plans'', paired with [[Rachmaninoff]]'s Piano Concerto No. 3.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://burnhamplan100.uchicago.edu/history_future/burnham_pavilions|title=The Burnham Pavilions in Millennium Park|accessdate=2009-07-29|publisher=The Burnham Plan Centennial|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20090512084452/http://burnhamplan100.uchicago.edu/history_future/burnham_pavilions <!--Added by H3llBot-->|archivedate=2009-05-12}}</ref> Also, the pavilion serves as host to the annual Chicago Winter Dance Festival. During the festival there is a month of free dance instructions behind the glass doors of the pavilion stage and free skating instruction at the [[McCormick Tribune Plaza & Ice Rink]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://abclocal.go.com/wls/story?section=resources&id=7246365|title=Chicago Winter Dance Festival|accessdate=2010-02-11|date=2010-02-07|publisher=[[WLS-TV|ABC Chicago]]}}</ref>

<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.explorechicago.org/city/en/about_the_city/press_room/chicago_office_of/Chicago_Winter_Dance_Festival.html|title= New This February: Chicago Winter Dance Festival Features Free Ice Skating Instruction, Late Night Dance Parties, Ice Dancing Demos, and Dance Lessons in Millennium Park |accessdate=2010-06-13|publisher=City of Chicago|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20100501025846/http://www.explorechicago.org/city/en/about_the_city/press_room/chicago_office_of/Chicago_Winter_Dance_Festival.html <!--Added by H3llBot-->|archivedate=2010-05-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.millenniumpark.org/documents/ChgWinterDance_REL12.11.09FINAL.pdf|title=New This February: Chicago Winter Dance Festival Features Free Ice Skating Instruction, Ice Dancing Performances, and Dance Lessons In Millennium Park|accessdate=2010-02-11|date=2009-12-11|publisher=Chicago Department of Cultural Affairs|author=Rowe, Joyce and Karen Vaughan}}</ref>

Among the highlights of the 2010 calendar is the screening of the [[BBC]]'s nature documentary ''[[Planet Earth Live]]'' on July 21, with live [[Grant Park Symphony Orchestra]] accompaniment featuring the [[Film score|score]] by five-time [[Academy Award]]-winning composer [[George Fenton]], who serves as conductor.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/pressoffice/bbcworldwide/worldwidestories/pressreleases/2010/03_march/planet_earth_live.shtml|title=BBC brings Planet Earth Live to U.S. with emmy-winning composer George Fenton |accessdate=2010-05-02|date=2010-01-03|publisher=[[BBC]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.grantparkmusicfestival.com/2010-season/planet-earth-live|title=Planet Earth Live|accessdate=2010-05-02|publisher=Grant Park Music Festival}}</ref><ref name=NdltpwGPMFtsab>{{cite news|url=http://www.chicagotribune.com/entertainment/music/ct-live-0218-classical-20100217,0,2661665.column|title=New director looks to partnerships with Grant Park Music Festival this summer and beyond|accessdate=2010-05-02|date=2010-02-17|author=von Rhein, John|work=[[Chicago Tribune]]}}</ref>

Among the artists who performed with the festival at the pavilion in the 2000s decade are [[soprano]]s [[Karina Gauvin]] and [[Erin Wall]], [[tenor]] [[Vittorio Grigolo]], [[pianist]] [[Stephen Hough]], [[violin]]ists [[Rachel Barton Pine]], [[James Ehnes]], [[Roby Lakatos]], [[Christian Tetzlaff]], and [[Pinchas Zukerman]], and [[vocalist]]s [[Otis Clay]], [[Mariza]], and [[Maria del Mar Bonet]].<ref>Macaluso, p. 206</ref> All [[rehearsal]]s at the pavilion are open to the public and well-attended.<ref>Macaluso, p. 203</ref> The festival is represented by a staff of trained guides, called [[Museum docent|docents]], that field questions and provide educational talks during the rehearsals.<ref>Macaluso, p. 216</ref>

Besides these public functions, the pavilion is available, as is the entire park, as a venue for private events year-round. The stage's glass and steel doors enable it to provide indoor space protected from the elements when necessary.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.millenniumpark.org/privaterentals/pritzker/|title=Private Rentals: Photo Galleries: Jay Pritzker Pavilion|accessdate=2008-06-13|publisher=City of Chicago|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080529050301/http://www.millenniumpark.org/privaterentals/pritzker/ <!--Added by H3llBot-->|archivedate=2008-05-29}}</ref> In addition, the pavilion has a Choral Rehearsal Room that can be rented.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.millenniumpark.org/privaterentals/choral/|title=Private Rentals: Photo Galleries: Choral Rehearsal Room|accessdate=2008-06-13|publisher=City of Chicago|archiveurl=http://web.archive.org/web/20080529050243/http://www.millenniumpark.org/privaterentals/choral/ <!--Added by H3llBot-->|archivedate=2008-05-29}}</ref>

